  <body>
    <div class='wrap'>
      <header>
        <div id='dropdown'>
          <input id="dropdown-check" type="checkbox" name="toggle" value="checked">

          <div id='dropdown-drawer'>
            {{> controls }}
          </div>

          <label id="dropdown-label" for="dropdown-check"></label>
        </div>

      </header>
    </div>

    <svg id='stage'></svg>

    <div class='wrap'>
      <footer>
        <p class="number-colors">
          <span class="color-0">0</span>
          <span class="color-1">1</span>
          <span class="color-2">2</span>
          <span class="color-3">3</span>
          <span class="color-4">4</span>
          <span class="color-5">5</span>
          <span class="color-6">6</span>
          <span class="color-7">7</span>
          <span class="color-8">8</span>
          <span class="color-9">9</span>
        </p>

        <p>This is an interactive data visualisation of the number &pi;. It's a
        derivative work based on the 2013 &pi;-day poster by <a
        href="https://twitter.com/MKrzywinski">Martin Krzywinski</a>, <a
      href='http://mkweb.bcgsc.ca/pi/piday'>http://mkweb.bcgsc.ca/pi/piday</a>.</p>

        <p>Each digit in the numbers are represented by a circle of a different
        color. Each circle contains a smaller circle colored according to the
        following digit. The colors are assigned as seen in the list above.</p>

        <p>Tap or click on the number symbols in the top to choose a subject.
        Use the controls to change the number of rows, columns, radius of- and
        spacing between circles. Tap or click the image to toggle connecting
        lines.</p>

        <p>Source code available on <a
          href="https://github.com/rhardih/winski"
          title="GitHub">GitHub</a>.</p>
      </footer>
    </div>

    <script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/d3/3.5.17/d3.min.js"></script>
    <script src="js/app.bundle.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
